radiographic_examinations.findings: The lung bases are clear. The liver is normal in morphology and signal intensity with no focal liver lesions and no ascites. There is cholelithiasis but no MR evidence of acute cholecystitis. The pancreas and kidneys are normal in morphology with no focal lesions. There is no evidence of biliary duct dilation or choledocholithiasis. A small accessory spleen is noted. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal adenopathy. No abdominal aortic aneurysm.
